<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Isaak Divynshield</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-23 12:02:25</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Lord Grimrot spawns in 2 forms.  He has a skeletal form which con'd blue to me at 38.  He dropped a (Lore) Pestilence Scythe and a (Lore, No Drop) Diseased Heart.  The other form is a Human Shadowknight that also con'd blue to me at 38. This form has ungodly magic resist. He melees in the 80dmg range as well. Be sure to have a group to take him down.  He dropped a (Lore) Pestilence Scythe as well as a (Lore, No Drop) Pestilence Scythe.  His spawn rate varies. He spawned as the skeleton and human form once in the span of 4 hours.  The Quest starts in the Temple of Life. You need to talk to Cameland and ask him "What about Lord Grimrot." Note: You must have extremely high faction to get this quest or it may be broken.  At "Kindly" faction and "Warmly" he will not give you the quest.  Seems you may have to have "Fondly" faction for him to talk to you about it.  Hope this helps.  </font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Isaak Divynshield</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-25 10:22:27</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Well I just found out that "Fondly" faction no longer exists.  You need to have high "Warmly" faction for him to give you the quest.  And even if you get the quest from him that still doesn't mean he will give you the shield. I know numerous people that have gotten the quest from him and turned in the items and he ate them all leaving them with a "Thank you".  Seems like this quest maybe broken.  Or you need extremely high "Warmly" faction for the quest.  </font></td></tr></table>
